commit.message: CI: upgrade PyPy test runner from 3.9 to 3.10

migrate from external mock package to stdlib unittest.mock

It was moved to the stdlib in python 3.3, and the PyPI version is a
backport for python versions less than 3.3.

Stop holding migration temporary models in memory

Closes #463

Fix INSIDEOUT in older redises

- can't use SET ... NX GET
- math.random() used to be deterministic

Closes #449.

Better handle model families with abstracts in them

Should not try to call `family_profile()` for an abstract models
anymore. Also better works for multiple inheritance multi-table models,
which are not supported anyway though.

Closes #456.

Handle abstract models better

- do not attach signal handlers for abstract models anymore
- do not call `model_profile()` for abstract models, this raises
sometimes

Closes #442.

Make it work with Redis 6.x and older again

Fixes #449

Note that CacheopsRedis was dropped in 7.0 in CHANGELOG

Closes #448

Remove any references to StrictRedis

That one is an alias for 5 years or smth

Remove refering to run_tests.py

That one does not exist anynmore
